              </m:mrow>
              <m:mi>g</m:mi>
            </m:mfrac>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:mfenced>
      </m:mrow>
    </m:msqrt>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-18g">Note the striking similarity here with the free fall of a body under gravity from a height “H”. The time taken in free fall is same as the time of flight of projectile in this case. Now, the horizontal range of the projectile is given as :
</para>
<para id="element-18h">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mi>R</m:mi>
